---
By: Frater Achad
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 109
    Verse: 23
Tags:
  - Doubt
---
Man never encounters a mountain greater than doubt. Doubt is a deceiver. It
is as a thief in the night. Remove it ... do not let it come nigh your
dwelling. Never doubt. Learn to say and learn to mean it, “I am the all
of every thing good.”
